article.headline: IPFW 54, Indiana State 46
article.story: TERRE HAUTE, Ind. (AP) -- DeWitt Scott scored 17 points to lead IPFW to a 54-46 victory over Indiana State on Monday night as the Sycamores shot just 32 percent for the game. The loss was the third straight for Sycamores after they opened the season with eight straight victories. The Mastodons (3-11) opened up a 13-point second-half lead as they used a ball-control offense that saw Scott shoot 5-of-6 on 3-pointers. Quintin Carouthers added 11 points for IPFW, and Tyler Best had nine points and 11 rebounds as the Mastodons outrebounded Indiana State 36-26. Indiana State closed to within 48-46 with 1:07 remaining on a layup by Trent Wurtz, who led the Sycamores with 11 points. But a 3-pointer by Scott started a 6-0 run by IPFW to end the game.
